candidates.title: Add examples to Cargo
candidates.body:
This does a few things:

* Fixes having to manually change dependencies in ctapcli
* Adds all examples in the examples folder as cargo examples so they can be easily built
* Makes the new build tests build all examples so we can verify future PRs aren't breaking them

Closes #48

Closes #38

candidates.title: Linux support
candidates.body:
This improves Linux support in the repository by removing a lot of the linux specific code and instead relying on the crossplatform nature of `hidapi`. We use the libudev backend which does effectively what we were doing before, but since it happens in the dependency, we don't have to have conditional logic.

This means we can remove the entire fidokey_pi module and not worry about keeping it synchronized with fidopi.

It also means there is just less code to maintain and have to write separate tests for.

candidates.title: Remove Rust-Crypto Dependence
candidates.body:
The `rust-crypto` library is outdated and has many problems. For me, it's breaking my ability to compile code as it doesn't have a definition for `_rust_crypto_util_fixed_time_eq_asm` on `arm64`/`aarch64`.

I think it would probably be best to move away from using it, but I ran into an issue where `ring` does not support CBC mode. There have been issues opened for this for years so I don't expect it to change anytime soon meaning to move away entirely (and fix the compilation issues), we still need a replacement for AES256 CBC.

To address this I added new dependence on the `aes` and `block-modes` crates. This fully removes `rust-crypto` from the project.

It also passes tests but the tests aren't extensive. @gebogebogebo any good places to start on making sure I haven't broken anything?
